CONCLUSION: CPU inference is INVERSE scaling — more threads = slower.
OMP overhead dominates. Games run sequentially, no intra-game parallelism.
RECOMMENDATION: set OMP_NUM_THREADS=1 for all CPU inference (Elo tournament, panel eval).
PPO training (GPU): OMP matters less; keep at 2-4 for CPU preprocessing.

